This Python script copies all video files from one folder to another in Termux.  

ğŸš€ INSTALLATION & USAGE  

1. Open Termux  
2. Install Python:  
   pkg install python  
3. Create a folder for the project:  
   mkdir VideoBackup && cd VideoBackup  
4. Add a main file named "copy_videos.py"  
5. Write the script inside "copy_videos.py"  
6. Save and exit  
7. Run the program with:  
   python copy_videos.py  

ğŸ›  HOW IT WORKS  
âœ”ï¸ Copies all videos from `/sdcard/Videos` to `/sdcard/Backup_Videos`  
âœ”ï¸ Automatically creates the destination folder if it doesn't exist  
âœ”ï¸ Supports `.mp4`, `.avi`, `.mkv`, `.mov`, `.flv` formats  

